        public static Nibble constructFromBinStr(java.lang.String binStr)
        Returns a new Nibble object from a binary string. If the string size is less than 4, it will be right-padded with 0's. If it has more than 4 binary digits, the digits after 4 will be truncated. The string might contain underscores/spaces for readability purpose.
        Parameters:
        binStr - the given string of binary digits
        Returns:
        a new Nibble object

      • constructFromHexStr

        public static Nibble constructFromHexStr(java.lang.String hexStr)
        Returns a new Nibble object from a hex string. If the string is empty or null, it will be replaced with 0 (zero). If it has more than 1 hex digit, the digits after 1 will be truncated. The string might contain underscores/spaces for readability purpose.
        Parameters:
        hexStr - the given string of hex digit
        Returns:
        a new Bit object
